# Docs-First & Indexing

## Source Priority (strict)
1) Internal: `docs/`, `doc/`, `.cursor/`, ADR, README, API specs, DB migrations, tests, issues/PRs.
2) Cursor Indexing/Docs: all indexed documents with analyzed external links.
3) MCP servers (connected) for local and official sources.
4) Official vendor docs on the web.
5) Everything else = low trust.

## Evidence Block (required)
- Cite every key fact with at least one source.
- Volatile or disputed facts require ≥2 independent sources.

### Citation Format
- `[DOC: path#anchor Lx–Ly]`
- `[ADR: id/title]`
- `[API: openapi.yaml /paths/.../get]`
- `[IDX: title_or_alias → URL]`
- `[MCP: tool@server {query}]`
- `[EXT: domain.tld/page#section]`

## Checklist
- [ ] Search plan written (objective, key queries, target sections, validation criteria).
- [ ] Evidence block present and valid.
- [ ] Conflicts highlighted with references.

## Stop Conditions
- No coding if search plan or evidence block is missing.
